description:
Job Responsibilities:
• Supervise Sales team in China for Promotion, and sales and marketing;
• Liaise with the China manufacturing facilities for the sample development as well as delivery schedule
• Generate potential sales in new accounts that meet target budget ;
• Prepare & deliver professional presentations, proposal and marketing materials to potential client;
• Positive thinking, high degree of self-motivation, reliable and result-oriented;
• travel to mainland when required;
Requirement:
• 3 years marketing and sales experience in mainland market.
• F.5 or above.
• Good command of English, Chinese & Mandarin
Salary offer: HK$18,000 - HK$22,000 or above (depends on experience)
Interested parties, please apply together with a detailed resume, stating current and expected salary, and send it via Apply Now
APPLY NOW.  (Reference no and Company name).  Attractive remuneration will be offered in commensurate with qualifications and experience.
All personal information received will be treated in strict confidence for employment purpose only. Your application can be considered as unsuccessful if you have not been reached within 3 months. On the other hand, it may be transferred to other companies of our group for job openings. Unsuccessful applications will be destroyed for a period not more than 12 months.

Job Description

Locate new business opportunities as potential digital marketing products both independently and under the guidance of team leader;
Prospecting, identifying and acquiring new HK based clients for selling online marketing advertising solutions (e.g. WeChat/China Advertising/China KOLs,etc);
Follow up sales Leads, prepare sales pitch and agreements with marketing team;
Maintain good relationships with clients, regular review and up-selling various advertising solutions to enhance their advertising performance/effect;
Execute inhouse media investment plan by working closely with Marketing Director to enhance the market impact of Our Company;
Manage clients’ projects, including defining deliverables, schedule and setting milestones, resources planning, coordinating internal resources, expectation management, launch, KPI tracking and post-campaign evaluation, etc.

The Successful Applicant

1-4 years Sales or Marketing / Advertising / PR experience;
Online-media savvy is a big advantage;
Knowledge in China media (social media, KOLs, Tencent, Douyin, Xiaohongshu, Video platform, etc), but not a must, training will be delivered;
Creative, Dynamic, embracing changes personally;
Good communication skills in both English & Chinese;
Immediate availability is preferred;
Candidate with higher qualification and relevant working experience will be considered as Senior Business Development Executive / Assistant Business Development Manager.

What's On Offer

Attractive Remuneration Package and Benefits
Incentive & commission schemes will be offered
5-day work
Bank Holidays and other special leave (e.g. Birthday Leave, Wedding Leave and Family Leave, etc.)
Medical Insurance
Sales and Product training will be provided
Team Building Activities
Opportunity for Job Promotion
Friendly Work Environment
Interest parties please send your CV with availability, current and expected salary to us.

**Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only**

Responsibilities:


Explore new business opportunities through cold call, participation in fairs and website checking and maintain a solid client rapport;
Be well-versed in preparing PowerPoint presentation;
Participate in client meeting and client visit;
Provide contribution to sustain current clients;
Ad hoc project assigned.

Requirements:


Higher Diploma or above in BBA, Science and Pharmaceutical or related disciplines;
Good interpersonal and communication skills to establish good relationship with clients;
Well-organized, proactive, aggressive;
Initiative, self-motivated and strong business sense;
Excellent spoken and written English & Mandarin;
Fresh graduate will also be considered;

We offer attractive remuneration package and excellent career opportunities to the right candidates. Interested parties please send your full resume with availability, current and expected salary to our HR Department.

Welcome to visit our company website http://www.cmatesting.org/ for more information.

We are an Equal Opportunities Employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. All Personal data collected will be kept in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose only.

Job Descriptions:  

Handle customers' enquiries, provide product information;
Follow customers' developments and provide advices;
Arrange customer-visit and build up relationship; 
Prepare sales reports, analysis and sales forecast;
Assist managers in various kinds of sales-related programs;
Assist in ad hoc duties as assigned, i.e. market research, survey, etc.;
Provide supporting in marketing activities and events

Requirements：

Degree holder is preferred;
Oversea University graduate or above is welcome;
Minimum 1 year working experience preferred;
Good communication skills with analytical mind;
A self-confident, customer-oriented, outgoing energetic team player with good learning attitude are preferred;
Good command of spoken and written English & Chinese (Cantonese and Mandarin);

 We Offer:

5 days work 
Guaranteed Basic Income + Monthly Bonus + Year-end Bonus
A fast-paced environment where continuous learning keeps us competitive
Flexible healthcare packages, including hospitalisation and outpatient benefits

We offer competitive remuneration and benefits, holidays, stable working environment to the right candidates. Interested parties please click "Apply Now" and send your full resume with expected salary to us.

*All personal data collected will be kept strictly confidential and used for recruitment-related purpose only.

Wholesale Banking COO Office

Hang Seng's Wholesale Banking business provides a broad spectrum of financing solutions to large corporations and financial institutions. As a strategic financial partner to corporate customers, Hang Seng offers a comprehensive range of products and services including bilateral and syndication loans, project financing, property development financing, property investment loans, working capital financing, trade financing, cash management and treasury products. Our experienced and knowledgeable professionals understand the specific requirements of our customers and are committed to providing tailor-made financial packages in their best interests.

We are currently seeking a high caliber professional to join our department as Proposition Manager.


Principal responsibilities

Perform analysis and provide key insights on portfolio management in managing Wholesale lending assets to optimize balance sheet capacity with focusing on capital efficiency and reward;
Assist in the execution of lending related initiatives which support business strategies and achieve financial goal;
Oversee the regulatory compliance related to credit and lending and responsible for related regulatory returns;
Drive and coordinate the IT enhancement, digital lending and data management projects;
Ensure the timely and quality deliverables to meet the expectation of our key stakeholders

Requirements

University degree in a related discipline or other relevant qualifications; 
Minimum of 5 years' experience in banking industry, preferably with experience in lending proposition, business development / business management; 
Sound knowledge in portfolio management, Bank’s governance framework and regulatory requirements on corporate customers; 
Strong attentiveness to detail, resilient and ability to work responsibly in a dynamic environment; 
Creative, curious and with sound analytical and problem solving skills; 
Ability to manage multiple stakeholders and manage conflicts, high connectivity, capable to drive change and transformation effectively; 
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese; 
Great sense of ownership and servicing mindset to ensure efficient and effective customer service processes
If you would like to explore other opportunities at Hang Seng Hong Kong, please visit www.hangseng.com/careers/ for details.
The health and safety of our employees and candidates is very important to us. Due to the current situation related to the Novel Coronavirus (2019-nCoV), we’re leveraging our digital capabilities to ensure we can continue to recruit top talent at the HSBC Group. As your application progresses, you may be asked to use one of our digital tools to help you through your recruitment journey. If so, one of our Resourcing colleagues will explain how our video-interviewing technology will be used throughout the recruitment process and will be on hand to answer any questions you might have.
All information provided by applicants will be used only for recruitment purposes and will be used strictly in accordance with the Bank's personal data policies, a copy of which may be obtained by the applicant upon request. Unless otherwise instructed in writing by the applicant concerned, applicants may be considered for other suitable positions within the Bank and its related companies. The personal data of unsuccessful job applicants may be retained for a maximum of two years from the date when the job application is rejected and such data may be retained for a longer period if there is a subsisting reason that obliges the Bank to do so, after which the personal data will be destroyed.

Responsible for promoting IT Solutions and AI products to Public Utility and or Education sector;
Degree or diploma holder with at least 5 years’ sales experience in I.T. & AI solutions;
Able to develop opportunities within assigned account territory and explore new accounts;
Solid track records in account development and management especially in Public Utility and or Education sector
Self motivated and able to lead a small team in conducting sales and business development activities;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese (Mandarin and Cantonese) with strong presentation skill is a must. 
Please send your full detailed resume with expected salary and date available to The Human Resources Manager, NEC Hong Kong Limited, 25th Floor, The Metropolis Tower, 10 Metropolis Drive, Hunghom, Kowloon or by e-mail.



Personal data provided by job applicant will be used strictly in accordance with employer's personal data policy, a copy of which will be provided immediately upon request.

To become a digital expertise in our Company, you will enjoy our attractive benefits:

Competitive remuneration package
Performance Bonus
Medical Insurance
5-day work per week
Flexi-working hour
General Holiday, Annual Leave, Family Care Leave and Anniversary Leave
Casual wear in office
Friendly working environment
The Job


To sell and market a full range of digital advertising solutions to advertisers/ad agencies;
Candidates with more China digital marketing background will focus on China marketing solutions, like WeChat, Weibo and Xiaohungshu;
To develop a comprehensive media plan, from concept to execution, on multiple digital platforms to meet clients’ business needs;
To develop and deliver presentations and proposals to target clients;
To identify and recruit new business opportunities;
To achieve and exceed sales targets;

The Person


Tertiary education in any discipline with 1-2+ years’ work experience;
Knowledge in Digital Marketing Solution will be an advantage;
Analytical sense and detailed oriented;
Strong initiative, aggressive, result-oriented and willing to take challenges;
Good telephone manner with positive attitude and customer-oriented;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese;
Result oriented, self-motivated individual who is confident and competitive with a strong passion on digital marketing;
Candidates with more experience in online media will be considered as “Account Manager or Senior Account Manager”
Please send your application with full resume stating your present and expected salary to the Company by clicking on the "Apply now". Please also quote the reference number of the applied position in the subject field.
